-- Differential smoke: DELIBERATE disagreement, used with --expect-disagree to
-- verify the runner's detection path stays alive. Each backend runs in its own
-- process at a different moment, so a microsecond-resolution timestamp printed
-- as an INTEGER (integers display exactly; float %g formatting would round the
-- differences away) can never agree across backends.

int_of_float (Sys.time () * 1000000.0)
